==English==

===Etymology===

[[micro-]] + [[neighborhood]] ([[neighbor]] + [[-hood]])


===Noun===
'''microneighborhood'''
:#A very small urban [[neighborhood]], usually extending the length of a [[city block]] or smaller.
::'''examples:'''
::''With three Indian restaurants on Street X, the area is establishing itself as a microneighborhood.''
 
===Usage note===
Has been used in the [[w:New York Times]], where it has been said to represent a new pattern of urban development.

